                <div class="container"> 
                    <h3>Purpose</h3>
                <p>Create ideas that can potentially be converted into a business opportunity or
                    lead to IPR by conducting an event ‘Idea-Rise ‘@EDC-RIT involving students of all
                    departments. The proposed dates for this event this academic year should ideally end
                    within 20 th December 2019. (Follow-up sessions in even semester till Open Day Project
                    Exhibition: Pradarshana 2020)
                </p>
                </div>
                <div class="container">
                       <h3>What is ‘Idea-Rise’?</h3>
                <p>
                    Entrepreneurship and start-ups sound great as buzzwords but without proper thought
                    and focus they are as good as the water mirage on the road. To remove this mirage and
                    create a real oasis of talent, we at EDC RIT bring to you ‘IDEA-RISE’
                </p>
                <p>
                    IDEA-RISE is an entrepreneurship event which encourages students from various
                    departments and backgrounds to pitch in their ideas, identifying a real world problem
                    something as simple as getting food at your doorstep which we can’t imagine in any
                    way besides Zomato or Swiggy now.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We want to provide not only a platform for these students but also expert guidance so
                    that in this sea of noise, we add a strong footing and contribute to a functional startup
                    culture.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The main aim of the IDEA-RISE is to encourage students to identify problems which
                    can be converted into a business opportunity. Apply technology to find solutions to solve
                    this problem.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The intent of this event is:
                    <ul class="middle">
                        <li>Enable the students to imbibe the spirit of field work and research. Through this
                            camp the students will need to meet the societal entities to get a first-hand
                            understanding of the nature of the work they do.
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    E.g. To use technology to tackle the problem of garbage
                                    collection and disposal, the student teams will have to interact with
                                    the actual garbage collectors or BBMP employees.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Instill the spirit of ‘innovative and creative thinking’ to figure out the details of how
                            to apply technology to solve the problem in hand.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Inculcate the spirit of entrepreneurship by identifying a real-world problem which
                            can potentially be converted into a business opportunity or IPR.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>






                </div>
                <div class="container" id="obj"> 
                        <h3>Overall objectives of ‘<strong>IDEA-RISE</strong>’</h3>
                <p>
                    Provide the students with a forum to identify and formulate a systematic approach to
                    solve the problem in hand. This involves two main stages.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <h4>
                        Stage 1: Problem Definition and Ideation – How to turn problems into
                        opportunities
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="middle">
                        <li>Form the initial problem statement</li>
                        <li>
                            Get to know their idea-solution end-user/customer, and identify their
                            needs
                        </li>
                        <li>Refine the problem statement to convert it into a business opportunity</li>
                        <li>
                            Present the final defined problem to a jury of professional business
                            people and experts.
                        </li>
                        <li>Selection of valid problems/idea</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <h4>Stage 2: Ideathon – How to apply technology to solve the problem</h4>
                    <ul class="middle">
                        <li>Research the newest technological trends to solve the problem</li>
                        <li>
                            Analyze and decide which technology to be used to build a prototype
                            model
                        </li>
                        <li>Ideate along with plans of how to develop a prototype model</li>
                        <li>Review what is already out there that could compete</li>
                        <li>Build a basic business model around the idea</li>
                        <li>
                            Present the final idea-solution for a jury of professional business people
                            and experts.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

                </div>
                
                <div class="container"> 
                        <h3>Steps in Planning:</h3>
                    <p>
                    <h4>Stage 1: Problem Identification</h4>
                    <ul class="middle">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Inauguration and Orientation:</strong> This step is to bring awareness of the
                            ‘IDEA-RISE’
                            initiative to students and faculty of RIT. It is basically a motivation step to declare the
                            plan of execution of the ‘IDEA-RISE’. (Tentative Date: 14 th November 2019 –
                            Thursday)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Registration:</strong> Team Size: 2 to 4 students. Interdisciplinary Teams are
                            encouraged.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Submission of the real-world problem:</strong> Four weeks’ time to visit the real
                            world with
                            people who face the problem and understand their difficulties. Submit an abstract
                            write-up of the problem with focus on how it can be converted into a business
                            opportunity. (Online Submission Date: 14 th December Midnight)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Selection of valid real-world problem:</strong> Online scrutiny the problems
                            submitted and
                            filter out the actual real world problems which can potentially lead to business
                            opportunity / IPR. (Tentative Date of Announcement: 28 th January 2020)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Announcement of Selected ideas and mentorship for pitch:</strong> The shortlisted
                            teams
                            would be provided workshop on preparation for the pitch to present their ideas in the
                            second round in front of evaluators.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <h4>Stage 2: Mentorship and Ideathon</h4>
                    <ul class="middle">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Ideathon Stage1:</strong> The teams undergone the pitch workshop have to present
                            their
                            ideas in front of the evaluators in the form of a presentation. (Tentative date: 14 th
                            February 2020)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Mentorship Program:</strong> The shortlisted teams undergo domain based mentorship
                            programs covering all the aspects of making a product. The series of workshops
                            conducted will offer the following insights:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Elevator Pitch- illustration</li>
                                <li>Basic concepts of business & finance</li>
                                <li>Business Entities, Laws & Regulations</li>
                                <li>Business Plan- Practical Insight</li>
                                <li>Operational Plan</li>
                                <li>Financial Plan- Overview</li>
                                <li>Financial Plan- Practical Aspects</li>
                                <li>Start-up Ethos & Dynamics</li>
                                <li>Start-up India – Action Plan</li>
                                <li>Start-up Funding</li>
                                <li>Intellectual Property Rights (IPR)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Prototype Building: </strong> This is the next logical step- convert the appreciated
                            good
                            ‘idea solutions’ into a product prototype. It could potentially lead to many
                            interdisciplinary projects during Pradarshana 2020. The potential of this venture is
                            the involvement of EDC, Funding Agencies resulting in startups and incubation at
                            RIT. It could also potentially lead to patenting & other IPR related activities. (Term
                            January 2020 – May 2020)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Ideathon Stage2:</strong> After the mentorship programs are completed for every
                            shortlisted
                            on the basis of domains, the final presentation is conducted where the teams have
                            to present their business model and prototype of the product in front of a panel of
                            judges and investors.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>


                </div>
